Olamilekan Agbeleshe a.k.a. Laycon on Sunday emerged winner of the Big Brother Naija Season 5 “Lockdown” Edition. Laycon who enjoyed massive support from many celebrities and fans floored other finalists, Nengi, Dorathy, Neo and vee to win the grand prize of N85 million and other consolation prizes. The season premiered on the 19th of June with 20 housemates and was aired for 71 days. 14 housemates were evicted and 1 disqualified leaving the grand prize of N85million to one of the remaining 5 housemates. The breakdown of the grand prize for BBNaija season five winner includes N30 million cash prize; a two-bedroom apartment courtesy Revolution Plus; a top of the range SUV from Nigerian automaker, Innoson Motors; a trip to Dublin courtesy Guinness; home appliances courtesy Scanfrost. Others are a trip to Dubai packaged by Travelbeta; a year’s supply of Indomie noodles, Munch it, and Colgate toothpaste; a year’s supply of Pepsi, a branded chiller, trip to watch the UEFA Champions League finale; and a brand new Oppo mobile smartphone.